  "Table salt does not actually contain any chlorine in its chemical formula": "",
  "Chloride ions are dangerous too but only in very large amounts consumed": "",
  "Chlorine gas (Cl2) and chloride ions (Cl-) have very different properties. When chlorine gains an electron to become chloride and bonds with sodium in salt (NaCl), it forms a completely different, safe substance.": "",
